label: "A Fabulous Decade. Montgomery to Memphis. A Woman's Viewpoint," Typewritten
description: Typewritten essay by Septima P. Clark describing specific incidents that made the decade of 1955 to 1968 fabulous, including Rosa Park's education at the Highlander Folk School, Dr. Martin Luther King's influence in Selma, Alabama, and issues regarding social psychology of the American power structure.
